==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reformer
<hw>Re*form"er</hw> <pr>(r?*f?rm"?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who effects a reformation or amendment; one who labors for, or
urges, reform; <as>as, a <ex>reformer</ex> of manners, or of
abuses</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.Hist.)</fld> <def>One of those who commenced
the reformation of religion in the sixteenth century, as Luther,
Melanchthon, Zwingli, and Calvin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reformist</ent>⟦br⟧
